==Swedish==
===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|['svɛ&#768;n:ɛ]}}

===Noun===
'''svenne'''

# a derogatory or humorous [[w:Swedish language|Swedish]] [[w:slang|slang]] term used by [[w:immigrants|immigrants]] in [[w:Sweden|Sweden]] in reference to ethnic Swedes. It originates from a [[nickname]] for ''Sven''. Although the term might be considered inevitably derogatory by some ethnic Swedes, it has also been adopted as a term of self description, suggesting a [[w:middle class]] background in an exclusively ethnic Swedish neighborhood.

In Swedish, the word has obtained two different meanings, which sometimes merge. One is referring to [[w:ethnicity|ethnicity]], merely indicating that the individual referred is an [[w:ethnic Swede|ethnic Swede]], and the other indicating that the individual referred is boring, shy and habitually conservative. Because the latter actually is a common viewpoint in Sweden, both different meanings are sometimes used by ethnic Swedes, often ironically.

